  "local_port": 60210,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What are the best TED Talks by youth?",
  "response": "TED has showcased numerous inspiring talks delivered by young voices who are making significant impacts in various fields. Here are some of the best TED Talks by youth that you might find particularly engaging and motivating:\n\n1. **Marley Dias \u2013 \u201cHow one young person can change what the world reads\u201d**\n   \n   Marley Dias shares her powerful journey of creating the #1000BlackGirlBooks campaign at just 11 years old. Frustrated by the lack of diversity in children's literature, she set out to collect and donate books featuring black girls, aiming to change the narrative and inspire future generations.\n\n   [Watch the Talk](https://www.ted.com/talks/marley_dias_how_one_young_person_can_change_what_the_world_reads)\n\n2. **Boyan Slat \u2013 \u201cA radical solution to ocean plastic\u201d**\n   \n   At a young age, Boyan Slat presented his innovative approach to tackling ocean plastic pollution. Founder of The Ocean Cleanup, Slat discusses his ambitious plan to develop advanced technologies to remove plastic from the oceans, highlighting both the challenges and the hope for a cleaner marine environment.\n\n   [Watch the Talk](https://www.ted.com/talks/boyan_slat_a_radical_solution_to_ocean_plastic)\n\n3. **Emma Gonzalez \u2013 \u201cWe call BS on the gun violence epidemic\u201d**\n   \n   Survivor of the Parkland school shooting, Emma Gonzalez delivers a heartfelt and impassioned plea for stronger gun control measures. Her talk emphasizes the urgent need for societal change to address the epidemic of gun violence affecting young people.\n\n   [Watch the Talk](https://www.ted.com/talks/emma_gonzalez_we_call_bs_on_the_gun_violence_epidemic)\n\n4. **Sahar Nasiri \u2013 \u201cPedal Power\u201d**\n   \n   Sahar Nasiri, a young Pakistani inventor, introduces her design for a human-powered water pump. Her innovative solution aims to provide sustainable and affordable access to clean water in developing communities, demonstrating how youthful ingenuity can address global challenges.\n\n   [Watch the Talk](https://www.ted.com/talks/sahar_nasiri_pedal_power)\n\n5. **Mari Copeny (Little Miss Flint) \u2013 \u201cWhat can little kids teach us about dealing with big problems\u201d**\n   \n   Mari Copeny, known as \"Little Miss Flint,\" speaks about her efforts to bring attention to the Flint water crisis. Her earnest appeal underscores the importance of listening to young voices and taking immediate action to resolve significant societal issues.\n\n   [Watch the Talk](https://www.ted.com/talks/mari_copeny_what_can_little_kids_teach_us_about_dealing_with_big_problems)\n\n6. **Sabrina Gonzalez Pasterski \u2013 \u201cFuture physicist on the path to the stars\u201d**\n   \n   Sabrina Gonzalez Pasterski, a prodigy in physics, discusses her aspirations and the future of scientific exploration. Her insights into advanced physics concepts and dedication to pushing the boundaries of knowledge are both enlightening and inspiring.\n\n   [Watch the Talk](https://www.ted.com/talks/sabrina_gonzalez_pasterski_future_physicist_on_the_path_to_the_stars)\n\n7. **Akshay Venkatesh \u2013 \u201cThe Mind of a Mathematical Genius\u201d**\n   \n   Though slightly older, Akshay Venkatesh began showcasing his mathematical prowess early on. In his talks, he delves into complex mathematical theories with clarity and passion, highlighting the beauty and intricacy of mathematics.\n\n   [Watch the Talk](https://www.ted.com/talks/akshay_venkatesh_the_mind_of_a_mathematical_genius)\n\nThese talks not only highlight the incredible talents and perspectives of young individuals but also inspire audiences to take action, think critically, and contribute positively to the world. For more youth-focused TED Talks, you can explore the [TED website\u2019s Young Voices section](https://www.ted.com/playlists/171/the_power_of_youth) where a wide range of presentations by young speakers are curated.",
